Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so in this first lecture,\N{\rChinese}好的，在这第一讲里，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.02,0:00:05.46,English,,0,0,0,,I want to ask a question.\N{\rChinese}我想提一个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.64,0:00:07.02,English,,0,0,0,,The question is,\N{\rChinese}问题是，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.34,0:00:11.04,English,,0,0,0,,why did humanity transition\N{\rChinese}为什么人类从狩猎采集社会转向农业？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.04,0:00:15.20,English,,0,0,0,,from hunter -gatherer society to agriculture?\N{\rChinese}好的？在传统范式里，一个范式。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.82,0:00:20.72,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And in the traditional paradigm, a paradigm.\N{\rChinese}Okay? And in the traditional paradigm, a paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.78,0:00:25.80,English,,0,0,0,,Paradigm is a very\N{\rChinese}范式是一个很精细的英文词，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.80,0:00:28.26,English,,0,0,0,,sophisticated English word, and\N{\rChinese}它的全部意思是故事或模型或理解。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.26,0:00:33.20,English,,0,0,0,,all it means is story or model or understanding.\N{\rChinese}all it means is story ormodel or understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.40,0:00:37.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So in a traditional story paradigm,\N{\rChinese}好的？在传统的故事范式里，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.54,0:00:39.76,English,,0,0,0,,we transitioned because\N{\rChinese}我们转变是因为
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.76,0:00:42.90,English,,0,0,0,,we're first hunter -gatherers\N{\rChinese}我们是最早的狩猎采集者
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.90,0:00:48.04,English,,0,0,0,,and we lived in groups of about 20 to 50 people\N{\rChinese}我们住在大约20到50人的小团体里
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.04,0:00:52.10,English,,0,0,0,,and we roamed the land looking for food.\N{\rChinese}我们在陆地上四处寻找食物
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.28,0:00:53.52,English,,0,0,0,,It was uncertain.\N{\rChinese}那时还不确定
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.82,0:00:57.98,English,,0,0,0,,It was unstable. And then suddenly there was a Revolution.\N{\rChinese}它不稳定。随后突然出现了一场革命。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.98,0:01:01.18,English,,0,0,0,,we discover farming and\N{\rChinese}我们发现了耕作，且
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.18,0:01:06.04,English,,0,0,0,,farming provided a stable source of food\N{\rChinese}耕作提供了稳定的食物来源
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.04,0:01:08.32,English,,0,0,0,,that we could control okay the word\N{\rChinese}那我们可以掌控的词是“驯化”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.32,0:01:13.92,English,,0,0,0,,we use is domestication okay domestication just means\N{\rChinese}驯化只是意味着
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.92,0:01:15.66,English,,0,0,0,,that we bring it under our control\N{\rChinese}我们把它纳入我们的掌控之中
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.66,0:01:18.68,English,,0,0,0,,and because\N{\rChinese}因为
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.68,0:01:22.08,English,,0,0,0,,of farming we can now create\N{\rChinese}由于耕作我们现在可以创造
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.08,0:01:27.30,English,,0,0,0,,more food than we need the word we use for this is surplus\N{\rChinese}多于需求的食物，称之为剩余
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.30,0:01:30.08,English,,0,0,0,,and because\N{\rChinese}因而
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.08,0:01:35.32,English,,0,0,0,,there's a surplus people now could do things besides farming\N{\rChinese}由于有剩余，人民现在可以做除耕作之外的事
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.32,0:01:39.46,English,,0,0,0,,so for example we could have leaders\N{\rChinese}例如，我们可以有领袖
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.46,0:01:40.92,English,,0,0,0,,which\N{\rChinese}哪一
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.92,0:01:44.96,English,,0,0,0,,creates the idea of politics right we could also have priests\N{\rChinese}创建政治概念，随后我们也能有祭司
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.96,0:01:46.30,English,,0,0,0,,which\N{\rChinese}which
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.30,0:01:51.70,English,,0,0,0,,introduces the idea of religion we can have creative people right\N{\rChinese}引入宗教概念，我们可以有创造性的人才
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.08,0:01:55.18,English,,0,0,0,,which then gives us arts and\N{\rChinese}随后产生艺术与…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.18,0:01:59.90,English,,0,0,0,,slowly over time these villages grew into cities\N{\rChinese}随着时间推移，这些村落发展成城镇
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.90,0:02:01.12,English,,0,0,0,,and because\N{\rChinese}并且
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.12,0:02:05.28,English,,0,0,0,,there was a lot of people in our surplus we could now have literature\N{\rChinese}因为我们有了剩余，人数多了，我们就能有文学
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.10,0:02:08.66,English,,0,0,0,,reading and writing so\N{\rChinese}阅读与书写
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.66,0:02:11.68,English,,0,0,0,,we can now store knowledge and then pass it from generation to generation\N{\rChinese}我们现在可以存储知识，并将其代代相传
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.68,0:02:15.56,English,,0,0,0,,and across cultures okay we're gonna have science\N{\rChinese}并且跨文化传递，随后便有了科学
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.56,0:02:17.58,English,,0,0,0,,and technology and\N{\rChinese}以及技术
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.58,0:02:23.00,English,,0,0,0,,slowly over the course of this process we create modernity,\N{\rChinese}在这一过程的推进中，慢慢地我们创造了现代性，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.04,0:02:27.78,English,,0,0,0,,okay? Which is the world that we live in today.\N{\rChinese}好吧？这就是我们今天所处的世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.84,0:02:30.98,English,,0,0,0,,So the pivotal step\N{\rChinese}于是关键一步是……
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.16,0:02:37.40,English,,0,0,0,,towards modernity was this transition into agriculture.\N{\rChinese}向现代性的过渡是这一次向农业的转变。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.26,0:02:43.24,English,,0,0,0,,And this is traditionally what we believed about the world.\N{\rChinese}这正是我们传统上对世界的理解。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.20,0:02:49.58,English,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, there's no evidence for this, okay?\N{\rChinese}不幸的是，这点没有证据，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.84,0:02:53.26,English,,0,0,0,,And in fact, the more evidence we collect,\N{\rChinese}而且，收集的证据越多，我们越发现这点不对。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.60,0:02:57.54,English,,0,0,0,,the more we realize this is not true.\N{\rChinese}事实上，】
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.50,0:02:59.64,English,,0,0,0,,In fact,\N{\rChinese}In fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.86,0:03:01.96,English,,0,0,0,,what we now know is it was\N{\rChinese}我们现在知道的是，它是……
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.96,0:03:05.22,English,,0,0,0,,actually pretty stupid to transition\N{\rChinese}实际上从狩猎采集转向农耕是相当愚蠢的……
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.22,0:03:09.72,English,,0,0,0,,from hunter -gatherer into farming, okay?\N{\rChinese}……好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.82,0:03:11.08,English,,0,0,0,,For a variety of reasons.\N{\rChinese}因为多种原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.28,0:03:14.20,English,,0,0,0,,The first reason is that when\N{\rChinese}第一个原因是，当……
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.20,0:03:17.90,English,,0,0,0,,you're a hunter -gatherer, it's actually a pretty easy life.\N{\rChinese}当你是狩猎采集者时，生活其实相当轻松。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.00,0:03:20.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Because there's food everywhere, okay?\N{\rChinese}好的？因为到处处都有食物，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.00,0:03:25.28,English,,0,0,0,,When you're a farmer, it's a hard life because you have to grow that food.\N{\rChinese}当你是农夫时，生活很辛苦，因为你得种那食物。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.60,0:03:29.68,English,,0,0,0,,So maybe as a hunter -gatherer, you're working maybe an hour a day,\N{\rChinese}所以说，狩猎采集者一天大约工作一小时。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.84,0:03:32.88,English,,0,0,0,,but as a farmer, you were working six, seven hours a day.\N{\rChinese}但当你是农夫时，你一天大约工作六七个小时。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.26,0:03:35.02,English,,0,0,0,,It was very hard to grow that food.\N{\rChinese}种那食物非常辛苦。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.84,0:03:39.00,English,,0,0,0,,So in the book Sapiens,\N{\rChinese}于是《万物生长》一书里说，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.20,0:03:40.98,English,,0,0,0,,the Israeli\N{\rChinese}以色列人
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.02,0:03:46.00,English,,0,0,0,,historian named Yoel Harari, he's very famous,\N{\rChinese}以色列人史学家约埃尔·哈拉里，他很有名气，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.24,0:03:49.64,English,,0,0,0,,Sapiens is also a very famous book, there's a very famous sentence, okay?\N{\rChinese}《万物生长》也是一本很有名气的书，有一句很有名气的话，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.74,0:03:53.58,English,,0,0,0,,The sentence is like this, we did not\N{\rChinese}句子是这样：我们没有驯化小麦。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.08,0:03:56.36,English,,0,0,0,,domesticate wheat.\N{\rChinese}小麦驯化了我们。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.66,0:04:02.20,English,,0,0,0,,Wheat domesticated us, okay?\N{\rChinese}好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.98,0:04:05.98,English,,0,0,0,,So we thought that we made wheat, okay,\N{\rChinese}于是我们认为我们把小麦——我们的食物——变成了奴隶。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.04,0:04:08.28,English,,0,0,0,,the food wheat, into our slave.\N{\rChinese}但实际上，…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.58,0:04:09.98,English,,0,0,0,,But in reality,\N{\rChinese}But in reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.30,0:04:13.48,English,,0,0,0,,wheat made us its slave.\N{\rChinese}小麦让我们成为它的奴隶。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.54,0:04:16.98,English,,0,0,0,,And the reasoning for this is this.\N{\rChinese}原因就是这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.12,0:04:21.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Out in nature, if you're wheat and you want to survive,\N{\rChinese}自然界里，如果你是小麦，想要存活，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.78,0:04:26.08,English,,0,0,0,,you have to make yourself attractive to other people and to animals, okay?\N{\rChinese}你得让自己对别人和动物都有吸引力，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.36,0:04:30.02,English,,0,0,0,,So you have to be tasty and you have to be easy to find.\N{\rChinese}所以你得好吃又容易被发现。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.48,0:04:31.72,English,,0,0,0,,You have to do a lot of work.\N{\rChinese}你得做很多工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.20,0:04:34.72,English,,0,0,0,,But when you're on a farm and you're wheat,\N{\rChinese}但当你在农场里，像小麦一样时，你只需躺下不动，让人类来做所有工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.94,0:04:39.14,English,,0,0,0,,you can just lay back, do nothing, and make humans do all the work.\N{\rChinese}好了？于是对人类来说是个好交易。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.06,0:04:43.62,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So it was a bad deal for humans\N{\rChinese}好的？于是对人类来说是个好交易。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.62,0:04:46.92,English,,0,0,0,,and a very good deal for wheat, okay?\N{\rChinese}并且对小麦来说是个非常好的交易，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.92,0:04:51.98,English,,0,0,0,,So that's the first problem. You actually do more work on the farm than you do as a hunter -gatherer.\N{\rChinese}于是这就是第一个问题。你在农场里做的工作比狩猎采集时多。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.32,0:04:55.66,English,,0,0,0,,Which means that now you have to have more children, right?\N{\rChinese}这意味着你现在需要多生孩子，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.76,0:04:58.70,English,,0,0,0,,You need to have labor to do all that work, which\N{\rChinese}你需要劳动力来完成所有工作，这
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.70,0:05:00.88,English,,0,0,0,,creates a problem of overpopulation.\N{\rChinese}导致人口过剩问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.74,0:05:05.04,English,,0,0,0,,Which means that you are using too much land and\N{\rChinese}这意味着你使用了过多的土地，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.04,0:05:07.88,English,,0,0,0,,then eventually the land becomes dead, okay?\N{\rChinese}于是土地最终变成了荒地，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.32,0:05:12.02,English,,0,0,0,,Or not arable anymore.\N{\rChinese}或者不再可耕种。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.36,0:05:16.74,English,,0,0,0,,So it's the first problem. Second problem is that we're able to\N{\rChinese}于是第一个问题。第二个问题是我们能做到
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.40,0:05:20.12,English,,0,0,0,,dig up the skeletons of hunter -gatherers and farmers.\N{\rChinese}挖掘狩猎采集者和农民的骨骼
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.42,0:05:23.24,English,,0,0,0,,And what we see is that\N{\rChinese}我们看到的是
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.24,0:05:27.22,English,,0,0,0,,hunter -gatherers are a lot taller than farmers.\N{\rChinese}狩猎采集者比农民高很多
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.72,0:05:32.12,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Protein, right?\N{\rChinese}为什么？蛋白？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.08,0:05:36.90,English,,0,0,0,,Food. As a hunter -gatherer, you have access to meat.\N{\rChinese}食物。作为狩猎采集者，你能吃到肉。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.86,0:05:41.88,English,,0,0,0,,You have access to fruits and nuts and vegetables, okay?\N{\rChinese}你能吃到水果、坚果和蔬菜，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.06,0:05:45.46,English,,0,0,0,,Your diet is varied and very nutritious.\N{\rChinese}你的饮食多样且非常有营养。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.06,0:05:47.38,English,,0,0,0,,But as a farmer, you have to have a lot of food.\N{\rChinese}但作为农夫，你必须有大量食物。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.38,0:05:50.58,English,,0,0,0,,You have to have a lot of food. You have to have a lot of nature. You have to have nature. You have to have nature. And as a farmer, you're eating only what you grow,\N{\rChinese}你必须有大量食物。你必须有大量自然。你必须有自然。你必须有自然。作为农夫，你只吃自己种的东西。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.78,0:05:53.26,English,,0,0,0,,which is mainly wheat and some vegetables, okay?\N{\rChinese}主要是小麦和一些蔬菜，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.52,0:05:55.08,English,,0,0,0,,So you're not getting that much nutrition.\N{\rChinese}所以你获得的营养不多。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.48,0:06:00.40,English,,0,0,0,,And the third problem is that as a farmer,\N{\rChinese}第三个问题是，作为农夫，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.74,0:06:06.26,English,,0,0,0,,you are much more likely to die early than if you're a hunter -gatherer.\N{\rChinese}你比狩猎采集者更容易早逝。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.82,0:06:10.74,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Have you guys been to a farm?\N{\rChinese}为什么？你们去过农场吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.22,0:06:13.12,English,,0,0,0,,What's the problem on a farm?\N{\rChinese}农场有什么问题？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.92,0:06:18.04,English,,0,0,0,,Exactly. Thank you. pigs, right?\N{\rChinese}好的。谢谢。猪，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.20,0:06:19.62,English,,0,0,0,,Animals, they're everywhere.\N{\rChinese}动物，它们无处不在。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.00,0:06:21.96,English,,0,0,0,,Plus, where do you put the garbage?\N{\rChinese}另外，垃圾放在哪里？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.38,0:06:23.96,English,,0,0,0,,Where do you go to the restroom, right?\N{\rChinese}你去洗手间的路怎么走？对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.34,0:06:29.38,English,,0,0,0,,So because people are together in a very unclean place,\N{\rChinese}所以因为人们聚集在一个非常不干净的地方，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.70,0:06:32.98,English,,0,0,0,,it's much more likely to contract disease and then die.\N{\rChinese}更可能感染疾病然后死亡。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.24,0:06:36.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So for these three reasons,\N{\rChinese}好的？所以这三点原因，转向农耕的过程，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.80,0:06:41.76,English,,0,0,0,,the transition from hunter -gatherer\N{\rChinese}猎人采集者到农耕的转变
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.76,0:06:44.74,English,,0,0,0,,to farming makes no sense.\N{\rChinese}农耕毫无意义。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.30,0:06:46.38,English,,0,0,0,,And even today,\N{\rChinese}即使到今天，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.38,0:06:49.88,English,,0,0,0,,we are not able to explain\N{\rChinese}我们无法向你解释这次转变的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.88,0:06:52.90,English,,0,0,0,,to you why this transition happened.\N{\rChinese}我们无法向你解释这次转变的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.62,0:06:58.96,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? We don't know why we did this. So\N{\rChinese}好的？我们不知道为什么会这么做。所以
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.96,0:07:04.24,English,,0,0,0,,the only thing we can do is construct theories as to why this might have happened.\N{\rChinese}唯一能做的就是构造理论来解释可能发生的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.60,0:07:08.18,English,,0,0,0,,So even though we can't go in the past and\N{\rChinese}于是即使我们无法回到过去去观察我们为何这么做，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.18,0:07:10.50,English,,0,0,0,,look at why we did this,\N{\rChinese}我们仍然可以做研究并收集证据，然后构造理论来解释这件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.72,0:07:13.90,English,,0,0,0,,we can do some research and collect evidence\N{\rChinese}我们可以做研究并收集证据
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.90,0:07:16.36,English,,0,0,0,,and then create theories as to why this happened.\N{\rChinese}然后构造理论来解释这件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.38,0:07:18.54,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So\N{\rChinese}好的？所以
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.54,0:07:22.58,English,,0,0,0,,there are four different disciplines from which we can collect evidence.\N{\rChinese}我们可以从四个不同的学科收集证据。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.38,0:07:25.70,English,,0,0,0,,The first discipline is called archaeology.\N{\rChinese}第一个学科叫做考古学。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.24,0:07:29.18,English,,0,0,0,,Archaeology is just the study of the past.\N{\rChinese}考古学就是研究过去的学科。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.54,0:07:34.28,English,,0,0,0,,So basically, you go and you dig stuff up and you see what you can find. Okay?\N{\rChinese}基本上就是去挖掘东西，看看能挖到什么。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.72,0:07:40.70,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe you can dig up someone's house or you can dig up someone's skeleton or someone's clothing.\N{\rChinese}也许你能挖出某人的房屋，或挖出某人的骨骸，或挖出某人的衣物。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.02,0:07:42.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And from that,\N{\rChinese}好的？从中你能推断过去发生的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.52,0:07:47.52,English,,0,0,0,,you're able to figure out what happened in the past. And so\N{\rChinese}于是，三条考古证据是……
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.52,0:07:51.18,English,,0,0,0,,three pieces of evidence from archaeology we\N{\rChinese}three pieces of evidence from archaeology we
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.18,0:07:55.72,English,,0,0,0,,will look at today are Gobekli Tepe, Jericho,\N{\rChinese}今天我们要看的地方是戈贝克利塔佩、耶利哥和卡塔尔霍耶克。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.10,0:07:58.32,English,,0,0,0,,and Katahaljóek.\N{\rChinese}好的？这些地方是……
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.44,0:08:01.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And these are places that\N{\rChinese}Okay? And theseare places that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.18,0:08:04.74,English,,0,0,0,,we've actually dug up and we know what life is like in these three places.\N{\rChinese}我们已经挖掘出来并且知道这三地的生活状况。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.68,0:08:07.08,English,,0,0,0,,So that's archaeology.\N{\rChinese}这就是考古学。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.66,0:08:10.04,English,,0,0,0,,Second discipline we can look at is anthropology.\N{\rChinese}第二个我们可以研究的学科是人类学。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.92,0:08:17.04,English,,0,0,0,,And anthropology is the study of other cultures.\N{\rChinese}人类学是研究其他文化的学科。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.66,0:08:22.08,English,,0,0,0,,So in other words, there are places still on this planet\N{\rChinese}换句话说，地球上还有一些地方，那里的人们仍然以狩猎采集的方式生活。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.08,0:08:25.52,English,,0,0,0,,where people live a hunter -gatherer lifestyle.\N{\rChinese}where people live a hunter -gatherer lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.58,0:08:29.52,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe in the Amazon, maybe in Australia,\N{\rChinese}也许在亚马逊，也许在澳洲，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.92,0:08:32.62,English,,0,0,0,,maybe in Africa. Okay? And so we're able to go and\N{\rChinese}也许在非洲。好了？于是我们可以去
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.62,0:08:35.96,English,,0,0,0,,study these people to understand why,\N{\rChinese}研究这些人，了解原因
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.42,0:08:39.20,English,,0,0,0,,how originally we thought\N{\rChinese}我们最初的想法
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.20,0:08:41.42,English,,0,0,0,,and why we might have transitioned into farming.\N{\rChinese}以及我们为何可能转向农耕
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.52,0:08:44.56,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So anthropology. The third field\N{\rChinese}好了？所以是人类学。第三个领域
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.56,0:08:50.42,English,,0,0,0,,that we can look at is psychology or neuroscience.\N{\rChinese}我们可以研究的第三个领域是心理学或神经科学。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.26,0:08:53.88,English,,0,0,0,,Basically how the brain works.\N{\rChinese}基本上就是大脑的工作原理。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.94,0:08:57.58,English,,0,0,0,,How do we feel? What motivates us?\N{\rChinese}我们是怎样感受？是什么驱动我们？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.72,0:08:59.34,English,,0,0,0,,Why do we behave the way we behave?\N{\rChinese}我们为什么会这样表现？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.42,0:09:02.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So that's a third field we can look at.\N{\rChinese}好了？这就是我们可以研究的第三个领域。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.48,0:09:06.10,English,,0,0,0,,The last field we can look at is primatology.\N{\rChinese}我们可以研究的最后一个领域是灵长类学。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.46,0:09:09.92,English,,0,0,0,,The study of primates.\N{\rChinese}灵长类的研究。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.10,0:09:13.12,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Or monkeys. Because guess what guys?\N{\rChinese}好了？或者猴子。因为猜猜看谁？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.32,0:09:15.30,English,,0,0,0,,We're monkeys. We're primates.\N{\rChinese}我们是猴子。我们是灵长类。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.78,0:09:18.80,English,,0,0,0,,995 007 percent of our DNA are monkey DNA.\N{\rChinese}95.00% 的 DNA 是猴子DNA。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.40,0:09:23.96,English,,0,0,0,,So we can look at certain groups of monkeys to understand how they behave.\N{\rChinese}我们可以研究某些猴子群体来了解它们的行为。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.26,0:09:28.50,English,,0,0,0,,And there are three types of primates that we look at very closely.\N{\rChinese}我们非常仔细地研究三种灵长类。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.62,0:09:29.98,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The first is gorillas.\N{\rChinese}好的？第一种是大猩猩。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.18,0:09:32.84,English,,0,0,0,,We also look at chimpanzees.\N{\rChinese}我们也研究黑猩猩。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.20,0:09:36.54,English,,0,0,0,,And we look at binaural bowls.\N{\rChinese}我们还研究双耳碗。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.72,0:09:39.98,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Chimpanzees and binaural bowls are very close to us.\N{\rChinese}好的？黑猩猩和双耳碗与我们非常接近。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.58,0:09:44.80,English,,0,0,0,,Genetically they're the closest to us of all the primates.\N{\rChinese}在基因上它们是所有灵长类中最接近我们的。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.56,0:09:50.22,English,,0,0,0,,So, by looking at these four different fields we're\N{\rChinese}所以，通过研究这四个不同的种类我们可以……
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.22,0:09:53.12,English,,0,0,0,,able to collect evidence to construct theories as\N{\rChinese}能够收集证据来构建理论
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.12,0:09:57.08,English,,0,0,0,,to why we transitioned from hunter -gatherer into farming.\N{\rChinese}为什么我们从狩猎采集转向农耕
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.26,0:10:02.06,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So now I will share some of these theories with you. And\N{\rChinese}好的？现在我会跟你分享其中的一些理论。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.06,0:10:07.74,English,,0,0,0,,again what's really important to understand is we don't know what happened.\N{\rChinese}再次，真正重要的是我们不知道发生了什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.84,0:10:09.68,English,,0,0,0,,We can only guess about what happened.\N{\rChinese}我们只能猜测发生了什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.96,0:10:14.68,English,,0,0,0,,So the first theory is the idea of coercion.\N{\rChinese}第一个理论是强制的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.58,0:10:18.72,English,,0,0,0,,okay. And what this basically means is that\N{\rChinese}好的。基本上这意味着……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.72,0:10:22.02,English,,0,0,0,,there's an elite group of people who didn't want to work\N{\rChinese}有一群精英人不想工作……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.54,0:10:24.40,English,,0,0,0,,So they made everyone else work\N{\rChinese}于是他们让其他人工作
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.94,0:10:29.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that's coercion and the evidence for this is\N{\rChinese}好的，以上就是强制，证据是……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.30,0:10:31.70,English,,0,0,0,,that well guess what?\N{\rChinese}那好，猜什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.00,0:10:33.56,English,,0,0,0,,Gorillas do this right?\N{\rChinese}大猩猩就是这么做的吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.70,0:10:36.62,English,,0,0,0,,If you study gorillas, you will see that\N{\rChinese}如果你研究大猩猩，你会发现……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.62,0:10:38.82,English,,0,0,0,,they always have an alpha male\N{\rChinese}它们总是有一个主雄性……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.48,0:10:42.06,English,,0,0,0,,The male who's bigger than everyone else and who\N{\rChinese}那位比其他人都大的雄性……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.06,0:10:44.70,English,,0,0,0,,makes everyone do all the work He just sits and\N{\rChinese}让大家都干完工，他自己坐着睡觉，但他得到所有女孩和所有食物
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.70,0:10:48.86,English,,0,0,0,,naps every day, but he gets all the girls and he gets all the food\N{\rChinese}好的，猴子们，那是第一个理论。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.42,0:10:52.94,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so gorillas That's the first theory.\N{\rChinese}第二个理论是战争。
